Package: cleanplots
Title: 'cleanplots' Color Scales and Theme for 'ggplot2'
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R:
    person("Trenton D.", "Mize", email = "tmize@purdue.edu",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Color scales, shape and linetype scales, a theme, and
    saving defaults for 'ggplot2' implementing the 'cleanplots' graphing
    scheme by Trenton D. Mize. Designed for clean, publication-ready
    figures with strong data visualization and accessibility defaults:
    colors are chosen to be colorblind-friendly and to remain
    distinguishable when printed in black and white, with matching marker
    shapes and line patterns that keep groups distinct across multiple
    visual channels. A companion scheme for Stata is available at
    <https://www.trentonmize.com/software/cleanplots>.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
